25/07/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- A Turkish court on Saturday (24 July) charged three railroad workers in connection with a train wreck that killed 37 people.
The train's guard, Koksal Coskun, was accused of negligence and ordered detained for the duration of the investigation;
its two drivers -- Fikret Karabulut and Recep Sonmez -- were also charged and detained.
Transport Minister Binali Yildirm says the train was travelling at 118km an hour Thursday evening when it derailed in an area where the speed limit was 80km an hour.
But a lawyer representing the accused told reporters that his clients had received a printed manual specifying that the speed limit in that particular area was 130km an hour.
(Reuters, AFP, NTV, AP, CNN - 24/07/04)
